Frequently Asked Questions for TELUS Corporation (NYSE:TU)
What is TELUS Corporation's stock symbol?

TELUS Corporation trades on the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) under the ticker symbol "TU."



How often does TELUS Corporation pay dividends? What is the dividend yield for TELUS Corporation?

TELUS Corporation declared a quarterly dividend on Thursday, May 11th. Shareholders of record on Friday, June 9th will be given a dividend of $0.4925 per share on Tuesday, July 4th. This represents a $1.97 annualized dividend and a yield of 5.42%. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Wednesday, June 7th. This is a boost from TELUS Corporation's previous quarterly dividend of $0.37.  View TELUS Corporation's Dividend History.



How were TELUS Corporation's earnings last quarter?

TELUS Corporation (NYSE:TU) announced its earnings results on Friday, August, 5th. The company reported $0.70 earnings per share for the quarter, topping the Thomson Reuters' consensus estimate of $0.69 by $0.01. The business had revenue of $3.15 billion for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $3.19 billion. TELUS Corporation had a return on equity of 19.11% and a net margin of 9.96%. The business's revenue for the quarter was up 1.5% compared to the same quarter last year. During the same period in the prior year, the company earned $0.66 EPS.  View TELUS Corporation's Earnings History.



When will TELUS Corporation make its next earnings announcement?

TELUS Corporation is scheduled to release their next quarterly earnings announcement on Friday, August, 11th 2017. View Earnings Estimates for TELUS Corporation.



Where is TELUS Corporation's stock going? Where will TELUS Corporation's stock price be in 2017?

6 brokerages have issued 12 month target prices for TELUS Corporation's shares. Their predictions range from $38.00 to $47.00. On average, they anticipate TELUS Corporation's share price to reach $42.50 in the next year. View Analyst Ratings for TELUS Corporation.



Who are some of TELUS Corporation's key competitors?

 Some companies that are related to TELUS Corporation include BCE (BCE), BT Group PLC (BT), Telefonica Brasil S.A. (VIV), Telecom Italia S.P.A. (TI), Level 3 Communications (LVLT), CenturyLink (CTL), Shaw Communications (SJR), KT Corporation (KT), PLDT (PHI), Telecom Argentina Stet - France Telecom S.A. (TEO), Neustar (NSR), Talktalk Telecom Group PLC (TALK), Frontier Communications Corporation (FTR), 8x8 (EGHT), ATN International (ATNI), Telecom plus PLC (TEP), Cincinnati Bell (CBB) and KCOM Group PLC (KCOM).



Who are TELUS Corporation's key executives?

TELUS Corporation's management team includes the folowing people: Richard H. Auchinleck, Independent Chairman of the BoardDarren Entwistle, President, Chief Executive Officer, DirectorDoug French, Chief Financial Officer, Executive Vice PresidentSandy McIntosh, Executive Vice President, People and Culture and Chief Human Resources OfficerPhil Bates, Executive Vice President - Business Transformation and OperationsJosh Andrew Blair, Chief Corporate Officer and Executive Vice President-TELUS Health, President, Business Solutions West and Chair-TELUS InternationalDavid Fuller, Executive Vice President and President, TELUS Consumer and Small Business SolutionsTony Geheran, Executive Vice President and President, Broadband NetworksFrancois Gratton, Executive Vice President, TELUS Partner Solutions and President, Business Solutions East and TELUS QuébecMonique Mercier, Executive Vice President, Corporate Affairs, and Chief Legal and Governance Officer



Who owns TELUS Corporation stock?

TELUS Corporation's stock is owned by a variety of of retail and institutional investors. Top institutional investors include Beutel Goodman & Co Ltd. (1.96%), CIBC Asset Management Inc (1.46%), Great West Life Assurance Co. Can (1.27%), Mawer Investment Management Ltd. (0.85%), APG Asset Management N.V. (0.37%) and Cardinal Capital Management Inc. (0.24%).  View Institutional Ownership Trends for TELUS Corporation.



Who sold TELUS Corporation stock? Who is selling TELUS Corporation stock?

TELUS Corporation's stock was sold by a variety of institutional investors in the last quarter, including Greystone Managed Investments Inc., Beutel Goodman & Co Ltd., Capstone Asset Management Co., NN Investment Partners Holdings N.V., Douglas Lane & Associates LLC, Mawer Investment Management Ltd., Clean Yield Group and Aperio Group LLC.  View Insider Buying and Selling for TELUS Corporation.



Who bought TELUS Corporation stock? Who is buying TELUS Corporation stock?

TELUS Corporation's stock was acquired by a variety of institutional investors in the last quarter, including Great West Life Assurance Co. Can, Russell Investments Group Ltd., CIBC Asset Management Inc, Hexavest Inc., Mn Services Vermogensbeheer B.V., Forsta AP Fonden, Cardinal Capital Management Inc. and Rothschild Asset Management Inc..  View Insider Buying and Selling for TELUS Corporation.



How do I buy TELUS Corporation stock? 

Shares of TELUS Corporation can be purchased through any online brokerage account. Popular online brokerages include Vanguard Brokerage Services, TD Ameritrade, E*TRADE, Scottrade, Fidelity and Charles Schwab. 



What is TELUS Corporation's stock price today?

One share of TELUS Corporation stock can currently be purchased for approximately $36.32.


